Description:

A financial analytics company called ProfitMatrix Pvt. Ltd. analyzes the daily profit/loss data of different departments across multiple branches.
The data is stored in a 2D matrix, where:
Each row represents a department
Each column represents revenue/loss for that day
Positive numbers indicate profit, and negative numbers indicate loss
The company wants to find the most profitable continuous block of days for a group of departments.
This continuous block forms a submatrix (rectangle) inside the original matrix.
Your task is to find the submatrix with the maximum total profit (sum of all its elements);
 A valid submatrix must:
Include consecutive rows and columns
Contain at least one element
Because rectangular in shape
The company needs only the maximum sum, not the submatrix itself.

Constraints:
Constraint	Description

1 ≤ R, C ≤ 200	R = number of rows, C = number of columns
−10⁴ ≤ mat[i][j] ≤ 10⁴	Profit or loss value
At least one positive or negative value	(Matrix can't be empty)
Output	Maximum submatrix sum (integer)
Time Complexity Desired	≤ O(R² × C)

Example:

Input:
mat = [ [ 1, 2, -1, -4, -20],
[-8, -3, 4, 2, 1], 
[ 3, 8, 10, 1, 3],
[-4, -1, 1, 7, -6] ]
 
Output:
29

Explanation:
The maximum sum submatrix is:

[4, 2, 1]
[10, 1, 3]
  [1, 7, -6]
If we add all the elements in this rectangle:

4 + 2 + 1 + 10 + 1 + 3 + 1 + 7 + (-6) = 29

Since this is the highest sum possible among all rectangular sections,
The maximum submatrix sum = 29

// Java Code

import java.util.*;
public class Main {
public static void main(String[] args) {
      Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
      int R = sc.nextInt();
      int C = sc.nextInt();
      int[][] mat = new int[R][C];
      for(int i=0; i<R; i++) {
           for(int j=0; j<C; j++) {
                     mat[i][j] = sc.nextInt();
            }
      }
int maxSum = Integer.MIN_VALUE;
for(int startRow=0; startRow<R; startRow++) {
    for(int startCol=0; startCol<C; startCol++) {
        for(int EndRow=0; EndRow<R; EndRow++) {
            for(int EndCol=0; EndCol<C; EndCol++) {
                int currentSum = 0;
                for(int i=startRow; i<EndRow; i++) {
                    for(int j=startCol; j<EndCol; j++) {
                        currentSum += mat[i][j];
                        maxSum = Math.max(maxSum, currentSum);
                     }
                 }
              }
          }
      }
   }
   System.out.println(maxSum);
   sc.close();
}
}








